# Desktop CodeMirror layout (vertical spacing)

- When styling the inbox markdown editor (`NoteMarkdownEditor`, CodeMirror 6 under `[data-app-surface='capture']`), **do not use vertical CSS margin** (`margin-top`, `margin-bottom`, `margin-block`) on elements whose height must match what CodeMirror measures for layout: `.cm-line` nodes, line decorations (for example `cm-md-*`), or block widget roots (for example `cm-vault-image-preview`).
- **Use `padding`** for vertical spacing instead. CodeMirror’s height map follows measurements that include padding and border but **exclude margin**; margin-only spacing creates a mismatch and breaks click/selection coordinates below that content.
- For background and rationale, see `specs/architecture/desktop-editor.md` (section “Vertical layout and click coordinates”).
- **WebKitGTK text:** do not drop **`-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased`** on capture inbox **`.cm-scroller`** without re-testing on Linux; see `specs/design/desktop-text-rendering.md` (symptom 7 and Rules table).
